videos.headline: Zion follows up miss with a 2-handed jam
videos.description: Zion Williamson misses a 3-pointer but crashes the boards and finishes with a dunk.

videos.headline: Barrett flushes fast-break dunk
videos.description: Tre Jones comes up with a steal and passes ahead to RJ Barrett who finishes with a slam.

videos.headline: Tre Jones heads to locker room after collision
videos.description: Tre Jones goes after a loose ball and runs into Frank Howard, forcing him to exit to the locker room. with a right shoulder injury.

videos.headline: Hughes back cuts for one-handed dunk
videos.description: Elijah Hughes cuts to the basket and throws down a powerful dunk.

videos.headline: Zion flexes after and-1 basket
videos.description: Zion Williamson finishes a layup through contact and celebrates with a flex.

videos.headline: Hughes beats buzzer from opposite free throw line
videos.description: Elijah Hughes heaves a 3/4 court 3-pointer at the buzzer that banks in for Syracuse.

videos.headline: Zion blocks shot into 1st row
videos.description: Zion Williamson rejects Oshae Brissett's layup attempt out of bounds.

videos.headline: Zion ignites Cameron Indoor with back-to-back baskets
videos.description: Zion Williamson knocks down an open 3-pointer then scores down low in the next possession.

videos.headline: Zion soars for chasedown block
videos.description: Zion Williamson chases down Elijah Hughes and blocks his layup off the backboard.

videos.headline: Battle breaks White's ankles
videos.description: Tyus Battle gets Jack White on his heels and sends him to the ground.

videos.headline: Zion ties Duke freshman single-game scoring record
videos.description: Zion Williamson muscles in a basket underneath to give him 34 points which ties the Duke freshman single-game scoring record

videos.headline: Battle misses 3-pointer at buzzer
videos.description: Tyus Battle pulls up for a 3-pointer at the buzzer and misses, sending the game into overtime.

videos.headline: Chukwu slams home alley-oop in overtime
videos.description: Paschal Chukwu rises up and flushes an alley-oop as Syracuse beats No. 1 Duke in overtime.

videos.headline: Battle: Syracuse 'locked in' to upset No. 1 Duke
videos.description: Tyus Battle credits his Syracuse teammates for being locked in as they pulled off the upset against No. 1 Duke.

videos.headline: Zion's 35 not enough in loss to Syracuse
videos.description: Zion Williamson goes off for 35 points on 12-of-20 shooting along with 10 rebounds, but Duke falls to Syracuse in overtime.

article.description: Tyus Battle scored a season-high 32 points, and Syracuse used its 2/3 zone defense to rattle No. 1 Duke in overtime as the Orange pulled off the upset, 95-91 on Monday night.
article.headline: Battle, Syracuse upset No. 1 Duke 95-91 in OT
article.linkText: Battle, Syracuse upset No. 1 Duke 95-91 in OT
article.story: DURHAM, N.C. -- Syracuse packed its patented 2/3 zone defense around Zion Williamson, and dared a depleted Duke team to win from the 3-point line. Without shooter Cameron Reddish, the top-ranked Blue Devils couldn't do it. And without point guard Tre Jones, their defense couldn't pressure the Orange, either. Tyus Battle scored a season-high 32 points, and Syracuse rattled Duke in overtime in a 95-91 upset on Monday night- the Blue Devils' first home loss as a No. 1 team to an opponent other than North Carolina. With Reddish out with flu-like symptoms and Jones suffering a right shoulder injury roughly 5 1/2 minutes in -- which coach Mike Krzyzewski said will keep him "out for a while" -- the Blue Devils were down two starters and became a completely different team. The Orange took full advantage, forcing the Blue Devils to attempt a school-record 43 3-pointers. They made only nine. And RJ Barrett finished with 23 points, but was 4 of 17 from 3-point range -- the second-most 3s ever taken by a Duke player and the most since Bobby Hurley's 18 against California in 1993. "When you get two guys hurt and injured, there is no game plan anymore," Krzyzewski said. "Our game plan was to pick them up full-court, put pressure on the ball, and that was working pretty well. Then, you're trying to survive, really." Paschal Chukwu added 10 points and a career-high 18 rebounds while Elijah Hughes added 20 points, Frank Howard finished with 16 and Oshae Brissett had 14 for the Orange (12-5, 3-1 Atlantic Coast Conference). "When (Chukwu) plays like that," coach Jim Boeheim said, "we're a different team." Syracuse held Duke to 2-of-8 shooting in overtime while earning its second victory at Cameron Indoor Stadium since 2016. "We were just letting them shoot the 3," Battle said. "Just backing up and trying to limit Zion's touches as much as possible." Battle's jumper about a minute into OT gave Syracuse the lead for good at 89-88. Duke followed that with four consecutive empty possessions -- three missed 3s and a turnover that Howard turned into an easy layup. Barrett's 3 pulled the Blue Devils to 93-91, but Chukwu countered with a dunk off a lob from Howard to make it a four-point game. Williamson had a career-high 35 points and 10 rebounds while playing two days after he was poked in the eye at Florida State. His free throw with 16.2 seconds left in regulation tied it at 85 for Duke (14-2, 3-1), but he missed a second go-ahead foul shot. Brissett grabbed the rebound for Syracuse, but Battle's 3-pointer before the buzzer bounced off the back iron. BIG PICTURE Syracuse: The Orange looked nothing like the group that shot a season-worst 31.6 percent in a home loss to Georgia Tech two nights earlier, and they felt slighted by oddsmakers who had them as 17-point underdogs. Battle said Boeheim mentioned it to them before the game. "`That's a 17-point spread. That's how much people respect you guys right now," Battle quoted Boeheim as saying. "We're competitors, so we took that really personal." Duke: The night took an ominous early turn for the Blue Devils, when Jones' collar bone separated from his shoulder blade during a collision with Howard as he chased a loose ball before the first TV timeout. That injury has the potential to be a big problem for Duke, depending on how long he's out, because he's tops in the ACC in assist-to-turnover ratio while also serving as an elite on-the-ball defender on a team that entered ranked third in Division I in Ken Pomeroy's defensive efficiency rankings. SHOT OF THE NIGHT The game might not have made it to overtime had the Orange not hit an 80-footer at the halftime buzzer. They got the ball back with 2.7 seconds left after Duke couldn't get a shot off. Hughes took the inbounds pass and initially dropped it before taking three dribbles and flinging it from three-quarter court. It swished through to pull the Orange within 49-48 at the break. KEY STAT Syracuse outscored Duke 89-77 after Jones was injured while shooting 45 percent in his absence. Jones had four steals when he was injured at the 14:23 mark of the first half. The rest of the Blue Devils combined for four steals for the entire game. TAKING OVER Barrett (30) and Williamson (20) combined to take 50 of the Blue Devils' 80 shots, with Barrett making eight and Williamson 12. The rest of Duke's players made 11 shots combined. "There's a burden that's placed on (Barrett) and Zion in that situation, because they know they have to carry more," Krzyzewski said. "And the fact that they tried to do that, I like that. We weren't successful enough to win, but the fact that they stepped forward and put it on the line, I like that." UP NEXT Syracuse: Hosts Pittsburgh on Saturday. Duke: Plays host to No. 4 Virginia on Saturday. --- More AP college basketball: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and https://twitter.com/AP-Top25
